modules.description: This module provides direct bindings for asynchronous I/O operations on Unix file descriptors, including reading from and writing to file descriptors in a non-blocking manner. It works with low-level data types such as `Unix.file_descr`, `bytes`, and integers for buffer management. Concrete use cases include handling network sockets, file I/O, and integrating with event-driven systems like Moonpool for scheduling asynchronous tasks.
